# Protected Files - Do Not Modify

Do not delete or modify the files in the `LICENSES` directory.

# Project Guidance

Read and follow [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) for:
- Primary references (PRD, CONTRIBUTING, architecture diagrams)
- Conventions (TDD, SOLID, Unix philosophy, no unsafe code, DRY)
- Quick links (exit codes, config precedence, adding plugins, etc.)

**DRY:** Use constants or config for reused values; avoid hard-coding. See AGENTS.md.

# TDD for AI Agents

AI agents: strict TDD for production Rust (`crates/**`) and Python script logic
(`scripts/**/*.py`). For Makefile/CI/packaging/docs-only changes, run
`make check-*` gates; do not add `read_text()` substring tests. See AGENTS.md,
CONTRIBUTING.md § Test scope and layering, and `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc`.

# Writing style

Do not use em dashes or en dashes in code comments or documentation.
Use `--` for em dashes and `-` for en dashes.

# Commit messages

Multi-item commit bodies: `-` bullets, one change per line, 72-char wrap.
Single cohesive change: prose paragraph, no bullets.
Full rules: CONTRIBUTING "Commit messages".

# SPDX headers

When adding SPDX headers manually, include a trailing blank line (not a
commented one) after the block so REUSE automation does not replace existing
header comments.
